90" data-id="1656408976790"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1657501771011" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1657501771011"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Are you a baseball enthusiast who's looking to increase your athletic performance? Weight lifting for baseball is a great way to take your game to the next level so you can hit the ball further, run harder, and play for longer.</p><p>This article will discuss how targeting major muscle groups will enable you to power up your game.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1677509396432" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1677509396432" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1657094583441" data-id="1657094583441"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677509396372" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1677509396372"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><strong>Weight lifting for baseball is an essential part of a player's development that is designed to help increase strength and power and improve speed, agility, and coordination. It focuses on developing strong core muscles that provide stability during the swing.</strong></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679233806954" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679233806954"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Weight-lifting builds muscle mass, increasing performance in all aspects of the game.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659069737862" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1659069737862" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/9f2134e7-a245-4528-92e6-3fe17a32d9f7/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/WBCM-weight-lifting-for-baseball.jpg" alt="WBCM Weight Lifting for Baseball" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="615" data-width="1000px" data-height="auto" title="WBCM Weight Lifting for Baseball" natural-width="1200" natural-height="615"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569813" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569813"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What's Strength Training for Baseball Players?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764626941" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673764626941" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>A baseball strength training program is an excellent way for players to improve their performance in the game. Baseball is a sport that requires explosive power, endurance, and agility.</p><p>A baseball weight-lifting program can help build strength in the major muscle groups, such as the core, shoulders, and legs, which are responsible for powering your baseball swing.</p><p>Weight-lifting will help you target each major muscle group and build the strength and power needed to improve your baseball performance.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1676126465389" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1676126465389"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Benefits of Strength Training For Baseball Players</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1676126586293" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1676126586293" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Weightlifting for baseball players is a great way to increase their performance in the game. Strength training can help build muscle mass, improve flexibility and stability, and increase power and speed.</p><p>There are numerous benefits for baseball players that lift weights.</p><p>A weight-lifting program will get you ahead in the game, from increased performance on the field to improved coordination and agility to help reduce the risk of injury.</p><p>Let's check out some of the main benefits of starting a baseball weight lifting workout below:</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679233857710" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679233857710"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Improved Baseball Batting Power</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783124871" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783124871" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Weight-lifting helps strengthen the major muscles in your arms, shoulders, back, and core responsible for providing power to your swing.</p><p>As those muscles become more robust and powerful, they will help you hit the ball farther and harder.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675081935903" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675081935903"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Higher Speed and Increased Agility</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675081937983" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675081937983" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Weight-lifting helps improve speed and agility on the field. Muscles can be isolated individually with exercises focusing on explosive movements like jumps, sprints, hops, and bounds.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783179181" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783179181"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Improved Core Strength</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783179558" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783179558" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><a href="https://5toolsportsscience.org/articles-1/2019/10/29/top-6-reasons-baseball-players-need-to-be-training-core" class="" target="_blank">Abdominal strength is crucial for baseball</a> skills. A strong core helps provide stability in your swing and will also help with overall balance and coordination on the field.</p><p>Adding weights to exercises like planks, bridges, and crunches can help target the core muscles and increase strength.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679234279075" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1679234279075" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/70ff250f-77f0-4bb5-b5f5-3a2b0e60705d/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/baseball-hitting.jpg" alt="Baceball player hit the bal" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1920" height="1281" data-width="auto" data-height="auto" title="Baceball player hit the bal" natural-width="1920" natural-height="1281"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679233997092" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679233997092"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Reduced Injury Risk</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679233997745" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679233997745" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Weight-lifting can help <a href="https://www.wdhospital.org/wdh/services-and-specialties/orthopedic-care/blog/injury-prevention-baseball-pitchers" class="" target="_blank">reduce the risk of injury</a> in baseball players. Stronger muscles and improved flexibility will help protect your joints from the forces of throwing, batting, and fielding.</p><p>This can help prevent overuse injuries common in repetitive sports like baseball. Weight lifting can also increase bone strength and structural stability, reducing the risk of impact-related injuries.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679391747825" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679391747825"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Improved Flexibility and Posture</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679391748259" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679391748259" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Weight-lifting can help improve flexibility, essential for proper form and technique when batting and throwing.</p><p>Strength exercises like lunges, squats, and calf raises can help increase the rotational power and range of motion in the muscles and joints. This will also help with posture by improving muscle strength and balance.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679391773971" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679391773971"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Improved Coordination</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679391774304" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679391774304" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Good coordination between your body and mind is essential for baseball. <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/juliewilcox/2012/05/31/health-benefits-weightlifting/?sh=7a17313d5721" class="" target="_blank">Weight-lifting will help</a> you improve the connection between the muscle fibers, joints, and brain as you move through different exercises.</p><p>This improved coordination can help with reaction time on the field and make complex movements easier to perform.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679391812951" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679391812951"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Higher Endurance and Stamina</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679391813376" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679391813376" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Weight-lifting can assist in building up your stamina and strength endurance as a whole.</p><p>Exercises involving explosive movements like cleans, snatches, and jumps will help build muscular and cardiovascular endurance. This can help you last longer on the field and keep up with the game's intensity.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679391832193" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679391832193"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Improved Balance and Stability</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679391832707" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679391832707" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Good balance is essential for baseball players. Weight-lifting exercises like single-leg deadlifts, squats, and lunges can help improve your balance and stability on the field.</p><p>This will increase dynamic movement, allowing you to roam freely during games.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392007360" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1679392007360" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/5dabfaec-58cf-492d-be96-f4ea7e1b9fb2/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Baseball-corner-player.jpg" alt="Baseball player performing hit the ball" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1920" height="1280" data-width="auto" data-height="auto" title="Baseball player performing hit the ball" natural-width="1920" natural-height="1280"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781867139" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675781867139"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Strength Training Exercises for Baseball Players</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678537765396" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678537765396"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Strength training for baseball players is critical to developing explosive power and preventing potential injuries. Weight training improves core muscles, speed, and agility, reduces injury risk, improves coordination and balance, increases endurance, and enhances stability.</p><p><br></p><p>Instead of avoiding weight training for baseball altogether or trying to lift heavier weights each week, a comprehensive conditioning program should focus on helping players become more explosive and agile while at the same time maintaining their rotational movements.</p><p><br></p><p>To this end, there is a range of must-do lifts for baseball players of any position, regardless of their individual needs.</p><p><br></p><p>Specifically, these lifts should target the entire body, emphasizing the lower body and core muscles for maximum performance gains and injury prevention.</p><p>Here are some of the best exercises for baseball players:</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1678537892122" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1678537892122" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678537634059" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678537634059"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Clean and Jerk</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678783232603" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678783232603"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The Clean is a core Olympic weight-lifting exercise that benefits baseball players. It is a <a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/fitness-exercise/compound-exercises" class="" target="_blank">compound exercise</a> that involves the use of multiple muscles to perform the lift correctly.</p><p><br></p><p>The exercise starts with a deadlift to bring the barbell up to hip level, then transitions into an explosive power clean movement by extending the hips and bringing the barbell up to shoulder level.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1677513191795" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1677513191795" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/9HyWjAk7fhY" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679391902766" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679391902766"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The barbell is then raised from the shoulder until it is directly above your head, this aspect of the movement is known as the jerk.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1678538052502" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1678538052502" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678538052545" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678538052545"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Snatch</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678538052585" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678538052585"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Snatch is another essential Olympic weight-lifting exercise for baseball players. Coordination is necessary for the smooth execution of this intricate motion and the power and speed to perform correctly.</p><p><br></p><p>The exercise starts with a deadlift to bring the barbell to hip level, then transitions into an explosive snatch movement.</p><p><br></p><p>This is achieved by quickly extending the hips and driving the barbell overhead while landing in a squat position at the bottom of each rep. This exercise will help to build power and full body explosiveness.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1678538052533" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1678538052533" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/UBc5N_-xdqo" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679236718227" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679236718227" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679236718240" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679236718240"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Overhead Press</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679236718280" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679236718280"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The Overhead Press is an essential weight-lifting exercise for baseball players, strengthening the upper body and core. This exercise involves pressing a barbell over your head from shoulder level to full extension of the arms above your head.</p><p><br></p><p>This move targets muscles such as the deltoids, triceps, traps, and abdominals. Regular exercise will help improve your upper body strength and stability on the field.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1679236718296" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1679236718296" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/bTUlua24b7E" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679236743592" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679236743592" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679236743643" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679236743643"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Deadlifts</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679236743594" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679236743594"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Deadlifts are a great way to build a solid foundation of the lower body and core muscle strength.</p><p><br></p><p>This exercise involves picking up a weighted barbell to waist height from the ground and then slowly lowering it back down.</p><p><br></p><p>The deadlift targets the hamstrings, glutes, lower back, and core muscles, all essential for explosive power on the baseball field.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1679236743651" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1679236743651" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/uK54qIygnII" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1678538250911" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1678538250911" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678538250872" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1678538250872"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Barbell Hip Thrust</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678538250923" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678538250923"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Barbell Hip Thrusts are an effective exercise for baseball players looking to increase their core and lower body strength.</p><p><br></p><p>This exercise engages the core muscles, thighs, hips, and buttocks (gluteus maximus, hamstrings, and quadriceps). This will improve your balance, stability, and power in all aspects of the game.</p><p><br></p><p>First, lay on the floor with a barbell across your hips. Lift the barbell off the ground by positioning your feet flat and driving through your heels. For maximum benefit, squeeze your glutes at the peak of the movement.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1678538250896" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1678538250896" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5S8SApGU_Lk" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679392054552" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679392054552" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392054606" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392054606"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-kettlebells" class="">Kettlebell</a> Swings</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392054549" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392054549"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Kettlebell swings are significant as the glutes, hamstrings, and abdominals all get a workout from this movement. The swinging motion helps to improve coordination and power throughout the entire body.</p><p><br></p><p>Holding a kettlebell with both hands is the first step in performing a Kettlebell Swing. Swing the kettlebell back between your legs as you hinge at the hips. Then drive through your heels as you push the kettlebell up and forward.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1679392054472" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1679392054472" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/1cVT3ee9mgU" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679392080379" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679392080379" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392080462" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392080462"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Renegade Rows</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392080421" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392080421"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Renegade Rows are an excellent exercise for baseball players looking to strengthen their upper body without compromising mobility.</p><p><br></p><p>This exercise works the entire back, including the lats, rhomboids, and traps muscles. The rowing motion helps to improve coordination and power throughout the entire body.</p><p><br></p><p>To perform a Renegade Row, start by positioning yourself in a push-up position with two dumbbells close to your hands. Keeping your core engaged, row one arm towards your chest and lower it to the starting position. Then repeat with the other arm.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1679392080463" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1679392080463" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OlpPaGyywyY" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679392097120" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679392097120" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392097110" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392097110"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Front Lunge</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392097115" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392097115"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Front Lunges are an effective exercise for players in baseball who want to develop more muscle and power in their legs. The gluteus, hamstrings, and quadriceps all get a workout with this move while also engaging the core to stabilize the movement.</p><p>This will help improve your balance, stability, and speed.</p><p><br></p><p>Stand tall with your feet hip-width apart to perform a Front Lunge. Step forward and bend the knee to a 90-degree angle, one leg at a time.</p><p><br></p><p>Then, to get back to the initial position, you should push off the front of your foot through the heel.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1679392097135" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1679392097135" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/rAOyVVv7kyQ" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679392113275" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679392113275" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392113228" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392113228"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Goblet Squats</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392113251" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392113251"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Goblet squats are a movement that trains the hamstrings, glutes, and quads and engages the core to stabilize the movement. Squatting is an excellent exercise as it develops strength and balances all over your body.</p><p><br></p><p>Start the Goblet Squat by holding a dumbbell or kettlebell in both hands close to your chest.</p><p><br></p><p>Lower your body until your thighs parallel the floor by pressing your hips back. You can return to square one by bringing your toes together and pushing off with your heels.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1679392113230" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1679392113230" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/MeIiIdhvXT4" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679392131176" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679392131176" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1678537892185" data-id="1678537892185"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392131210" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392131210"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Farmer's Walks</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679392131106" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1679392131106"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Baseball players who want to improve their strength and power should include Farmer's Walks in their movement patterns.</p><p><br></p><p>Shoulders, traps, abs, and legs all get a workout from this one simple move. The walking motion helps to improve coordination and power throughout the entire body.</p><p><br></p><p>Pick up two heavyweights in each hand to perform a Farmer's Walk. Keep your chest up and core engaged as you walk across the room. Then return to the starting position.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1679392131154" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1679392131154" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/rt17lmnaLSM" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1679392150730" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1679392150730" data-layout-lg="12" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div